Jul 19 2007 	Good price and location really great staff	The hotel is right on the Pulaski stop of the CTA and is about a 15 minute ride in to the Loop. For the price, the location is fantastic. You can park your car and just head straight into the city. The exterior looks like a standard motor lodge, but the rooms themselves are really nice and beautifully decorated. There's a fridge, a big TV with DVR capability, a desk, a bed with really soft and plentiful pillows. The high speed wireless internet was slow when I stayed there, but they were working on fixing it. The staff was incredibly friendly and helpful. The continental breakfast included coffee, donuts, and Dunkin Donuts egg sandwiches.	
